** The Company:   
** Part of a national group of companies this organisation is well known and respected for delivering complex technical projects across Qld and nationally, particularly in the water/wastewater and resources sectors. Ranging from graduate and junior engineers to highly experienced senior electrical and controls engineers their team is passionate about technology and delivering innovative, quality solutions to their clients. **   
  
The Role: **  
Use your experience of power system analysis and design to lead and deliver
robust and cost effective designs for projects in the water/wastewater and
resources sectors. Reporting to the Engineering Manager this is a
comprehensive and varied role:  

  * Plan, organise and conduct full reviews of design and documentation, and design changes 
  * Undertake power systems design and analysis including load flow, voltage drop, fault current and arc flash analysis 
  * Ensure adherence to project scope, Australian standards, regulatory, health, safety and environmental requirements 
  * Mentor and guide team members, encourage collaboration and continuous learning and improvement 
** ** Skills & Experience:   
** **

  * RPEQ or eligibility to obtain 
  * Power Simulation software - ideally SKM Power Tools, and AutoCAD 
  * Solid electrical engineering experience within the construction industry 
  * A trades background will be highly regarded 
  * Team lead, supervisory and mentoring experience 
